'''[[Alpine skiing]] at the [[2002 Winter Olympics]]''' consisted of ten events held 10–23 February in the [[United States]] near [[Salt Lake City]], [[Utah]]. The [[Downhill (ski competition)|downhill]], [[super-G]], and [[Alpine skiing combined|combined]] events were held at [[Snowbasin]], the [[giant slalom]]s at [[Park City Mountain Resort|Park City]], and the [[Slalom skiing|slalom]]s at adjacent [[Deer Valley Resort|Deer Valley]].<ref name=OfficialReport>{{cite web
 |title        = The Official Report of the XIX Olympic Winter Games – Salt Lake 2002
 |url          = http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/2002/SLC2002Results1.pdf
 |publisher    = LA84 Foundation
 |work         = Salt Lake Organizing Committee
 |year         = 2002
 |access-date   = 25 February 2014
 |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20140103193224/http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/2002/SLC2002Results1.pdf
 |archive-date = 3 January 2014
 |url-status   = dead
}}</ref><ref name="SR">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/winter/2002/ASK/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200417054400/https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/winter/2002/ASK/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=17 April 2020 |title=Alpine Skiing at the 2002 Salt Lake City Winter Games |access-date=31 March 2018 |work=Sports Reference}}</ref>

