[[File:2002 Nordic combined - 3.jpg|thumb|Nordic Combined cross-country skiing at Soldier Hollow.]]
[[File:Nordic combined 2002 - 4.jpg|thumb|Nordic Combined ski jumping at Park City.]]
[[Nordic combined]] at the [[2002 Winter Olympics]], consisted of three events held over ten days, from 9 February to 22 February. The ski jumping part took place in [[Park City, Utah|Park City]], while the cross-country part took place in [[Soldier Hollow]]. This was the first Winter Olympics to have two individual Nordic Combined events: the 7.5&nbsp;km individual normal hill (sprint) and the 15&nbsp;km individual large hill (individual).<ref name="SR">{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/winter/2002/NCO/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200417053939/https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/winter/2002/NCO/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=17 April 2020 |title=Nordic Combined at the 2002 Salt Lake City Winter Games |work=Sports Reference |access-date=8 September 2019}}</ref>

