'''[[Short track speed skating]] at the [[2002 Winter Olympics]]''' was held from 13 to 23 February. Eight events were contested at Salt Lake Ice Center (normally called [[Delta Center]]). Two new events were added for these games, with the men's and women's 1500 metres making debuts.<ref name=OfficialReport>{{cite web | title = Salt Lake City 2002 Official Report - Volume 3 | url = http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/2002/SLC2002Results3.pdf | publisher = LA84 Foundation | work = Salt Lake Organizing Committee | year = 2002 | access-date = 13 January 2014}}</ref><ref name="SR">{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/winter/2002/STK/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200417061543/https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/winter/2002/STK/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=17 April 2020 |title=Short Track Speed Skating at the 2002 Salt Lake City Winter Games |work=Sports Reference |access-date=12 November 2019}}</ref>

